viewer discretion is advised]

3
00:00:16,040 --> 00:00:18,040
♫A shark washes ashore♫

4
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:18,840
I forgot about that.

5
00:00:18,880 --> 00:00:20,840
I won't get to see Qin
during the semester break.

6
00:00:20,880 --> 00:00:24,000
Qin, please practice
with him during the break.

7
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:28,590
And you're here by yourself?

8
00:00:28,880 --> 00:00:29,880
Do you see anybody else with me?

9
00:00:32,320 --> 00:00:33,480
I need some advice.

10
00:00:33,520 --> 00:00:35,200
I'm serious about my singing.

11
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:37,400
I can't sing, and I don't know what to do.

12
00:00:37,920 --> 00:00:39,480
I don't want to be your burden.

13
00:00:39,920 --> 00:00:41,720
Do you want to practice singing at my place?

14
00:00:44,640 --> 00:00:46,100
You invited me to your place?!

15
00:01:00,160 --> 00:01:01,160
What's with the looking around?

16
00:01:02,040 --> 00:01:04,480
Well, I've never been here.

17
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:08,039
This is nothing special.

18
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:13,360
Your room smells nice.

19
00:01:14,720 --> 00:01:15,920
Nobody's room is as disgusting as yours.

20
00:01:18,120 --> 00:01:19,760
You've been to my place or something?

21
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:20,800
Don't just assume things.

22
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:28,200
Wow, you even got a teddy.

23
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:30,039
It looks so adorable!

24
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:31,720
It's from someone I flirted with.

25
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:41,360
And you're still keeping it.

26
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,600
I can tell the feeling is still there.

27
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:45,000
It's "someone I flirted with."

28
00:01:45,039 --> 00:01:46,240
We parted ways ages ago.

29
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:47,840
The teddy did nothing wrong.

30
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:51,520
Why should I throw it away?

31
00:01:52,720 --> 00:01:54,160
That stings me right in the chest.

32
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:33,040
♫I'm not leaving soon, so bear with me♫

33
00:02:33,579 --> 00:02:38,180
♫Wherever you are
is where I'll always be♫

34
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:42,079
♫Wherever you go, I'll find you eventually♫

35
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:44,400
♫You may push me away, but I won't flee♫

36
00:02:44,440 --> 00:02:47,440
♫Who would you love if it weren't me?♫

37
00:02:47,480 --> 00:02:49,720
♫So, wanna make a deal, maybe?♫

38
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:52,120
♫Alright, alright, don't worry♫

39
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:54,400
♫Just date me first, take it easy♫

40
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:56,800
♫I'll be so cute you'll fall naturally♫

41
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:59,120
♫No matter what, you'll always run into me♫

42
00:02:59,160 --> 00:03:01,520
♫Okay, okay, let it be♫

43
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:03,840
♫I know you're also into me,♫

44
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:06,360
♫Don't you feel the same? I can see♫

45
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:12,640
♫I'll keep on flirting,
don't try to avoid me♫

46
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:17,440
♫'Cause I won't stop
till you fall for me♫

47
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:22,000
♫I'll keep on flirting,
I won't stop, I guarantee♫

48
00:03:22,040 --> 00:03:28,440
♫I'll love you hard,
and once you say yes, I'll set you free♫

49
00:03:32,420 --> 00:03:37,280
♫No matter how far
or how long it takes,♫

50
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:42,760
♫I'll be there for you
when you're all alone♫

51
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:45,880
♫Every moment with you♫

52
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:49,920
♫Is enough to fill my heart♫

53
00:03:50,079 --> 00:03:53,240
♫Is enough to fill my heart♫

54
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:57,120
♫Is enough to fill my heart♫

55
00:03:57,280 --> 00:04:00,360
♫As we walk side by side♫

56
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:03,300
♫As we walk side by side♫

57
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:07,080
♫As we walk side by side♫

58
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:08,720
Mm.

59
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:10,350
Something like that.

60
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:12,400
How did I do?

61
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:14,120
You did fine.

62
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:15,640
Was it out of tune?

63
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,160
Not really.

64
00:04:21,959 --> 00:04:23,880
Do you have a prize for me?

65
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:31,720
You're crossing the line.

66
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,600
We'll call it here.

67
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:41,080
It's getting late.

68
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:34,520
Thank you.

69
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:54,440
Now, go back to your house.

70
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:58,360
I live in a condo, not a house.

71
00:05:59,080 --> 00:06:01,000
Whatever. Go to your condo already.

72
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:02,920
It's my older brother's, not mine.

73
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:04,520
My brother's name is Funan.

74
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,640
He's less adorable than me.

75
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:06,600
But he lives in our house.

76
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:07,520
Did I ask you any of that?

77
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:10,280
Just leave. I don't care.

78
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:14,720
Both my house and condo
are so far from here.

79
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:19,080
Would it be okay
if I spent the night here?

80
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:19,960
No.

81
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:23,200
Without hesitation, even?

82
00:06:24,060 --> 00:06:25,060
I understand.

83
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:27,480
Being here is beyond my wildest dreams.

84
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:31,440
Actually...

85
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:34,159
You're worried
I'd do nasty things to you, right?

86
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:35,680
Ow!

87
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:40,640
So dramatic.

88
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:45,840
Hey, let me see it.

89
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:48,320
Hey.

90
00:06:54,159 --> 00:06:55,640
You're worried about me, aren't you?

91
00:06:57,280 --> 00:06:58,120
I'm going to count to ten.

92
00:06:58,320 --> 00:06:59,480
Get out of my room,

93
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:00,800
or I won't let you come back.

94
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:02,920
Ten.

95
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:04,440
Nine.

96
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:05,920
Eight.

97
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:07,080
Seven.

98
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:08,920
Six.

99
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:11,360
Five.

100
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,600
You want me to send you
flying out of my room?

101
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:18,800
And I'll get to stay here
a bit longer, yes?

102
00:07:21,550 --> 00:07:23,350
A perfect dodge.

103
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,240
Okay! I'll leave now!

104
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:27,760
Next time, you should let me stay over.

105
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:37,440
I wasn't finished.

106
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:38,960
I made you blush, didn't I?

107
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:58,240
Mami?

108
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:01,680
Hello, Mami?

109
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:02,840
Hello, Duang.

110
00:08:03,140 --> 00:08:04,440
You called me.

111
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:06,160
You miss me, don't you?

112
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:08,360
Well, of course, I do!

113
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:10,080
You're on your semester break, correct?

114
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:12,240
Come home and see me, will you?

115
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:13,280
Mm...

116
00:08:13,460 --> 00:08:15,080
I'm actually thinking of coming home.

117
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:17,720
I really, really miss you, Mami.

118
00:08:17,760 --> 00:08:19,480
What? Really?

119
00:08:19,660 --> 00:08:21,840
How about coming home right now?

120
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:23,240
I'll make your favorite soup for you.

121
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:26,000
I'd better get going, then.

122
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:27,880
I'll be there in a flash.

123
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:58,600
Why are you smiling all by yourself?

124
00:08:58,640 --> 00:09:01,000
You didn't get up when I woke you up
for our workout this morning.

125
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:02,920
Now that you're home,

126
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:04,480
you're not going to work out with me?

127
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:06,920
Look at Funan, he joined me.

128
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:11,120
You'd better take care of
your health, alright?

129
00:09:13,740 --> 00:09:15,080
It's too early in the morning.

130
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:18,720
I just want to take a long sleep
now that I'm home, Dad.

131
00:09:20,580 --> 00:09:21,580
What's on your phone, huh?

132
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,080
Why were you smiling?

133
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:24,120
Let me see it.

134
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,600
Nope. It was nothing.

135
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:30,000
I was doomscrolling.

136
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:32,880
That's not a good way
to spend your time.

137
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:34,680
You've been like this
since you were little.

138
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:37,000
You're being too laid-back, Duang.

139
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:46,200
Why not stay home
now that you're on a break?

140
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:49,240
I told Mami I have a university event.

141
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:50,640
An event? What is it?

142
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,720
Why does it have to take place
during the break?

143
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:55,360
I asked Mami,

144
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:57,080
and she told me to ask you.

145
00:09:58,560 --> 00:10:00,520
Are you hiding something from us, hm?

146
00:10:00,560 --> 00:10:02,680
Or you've been doing something trivial?

147
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:03,480
Nope.

148
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:05,000
I wasn't lying.

149
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:06,400
It's not anything trivial either.

150
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:08,480
I'm actually working
on a university project.

151
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:10,440
My seniors needed my help.

152
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:12,800
Can you really trust the seniors?

153
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:13,640
He's right.

154
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:15,080
Can you really trust them?

155
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:16,880
I think...

156
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:18,920
You shouldn't listen
to what they say too much.

157
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:22,640
I know!

158
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:24,440
I'm a grown-up now.

159
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:28,000
I know my way around things.

160
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:30,120
Oh, come here, you.

161
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:31,480
You know your way around things,

162
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:32,680
yet you're so forgetful.

163
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:34,920
Last month,
you forgot to pay my condo bills.

164
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:40,640
What would you do
if it weren't for your brother?

165
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:45,680
Okay.

166
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:47,760
I'm a lost cause.

167
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:56,880
Mami!

168
00:10:56,920 --> 00:10:58,120
I have something to tell you!

169
00:10:58,160 --> 00:10:59,080
Duang!

170
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:01,480
What are you cooking?
It smells delightful!

171
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:03,040
Dad, I'm going to take a shower, okay?

172
00:11:03,220 --> 00:11:04,540
Hey, Funan!

173
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:06,720
Mami!

174
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:07,920
What is it, Duang?!

175
00:11:09,900 --> 00:11:11,920
Dad and Funan picked on me.

176
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,440
What? Why the outburst?

177
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:15,160
They always tease you this way, no?

178
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:19,240
Oh, wow!

179
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:22,160
Who made all of these?
They look so tasty.

180
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:24,080
Well, you said that you wanted to have

181
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:25,880
Betong chicken
and spicy salad with salted egg.

182
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:27,360
So I made them just for you.

183
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,400
Oh, you're right.

184
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:30,160
I love you so much, Mami.

185
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:31,640
Eat up and enjoy, Duang.

186
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:39,200
Oh, Qin?

187
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:42,360
- Are you back from the condo?
- Hello, son.

188
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:43,200
Here.

189
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:45,040
Have some fruit.

190
00:11:48,680 --> 00:11:50,120
Here you go, son.

191
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:52,720
Thank you.

192
00:11:52,760 --> 00:11:53,840
Here's yours, honey.

193
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,480
Thank you, sweetie.

194
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:10,290
This is Betong chicken.

195
00:12:10,330 --> 00:12:13,690
Although it doesn't look lovely,
it sure looks tasty,

196
00:12:13,730 --> 00:12:15,210
just like me.

197
00:12:16,770 --> 00:12:19,250
Then there's
spicy salad with salted egg, my favorite.

198
00:12:19,970 --> 00:12:22,170
I'm about to have breakfast.

199
00:12:22,530 --> 00:12:24,730
I wish you were here with me.

200
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:30,560
You're glued to your phone, aren't you?

201
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:36,320
Are you glued to the phone
or someone you're talking to?

202
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:37,960
I want to know who it is now.

203
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:40,640
I'll introduce the person to you,

204
00:12:40,680 --> 00:12:42,080
but I'm not sure
if the person would say yes.

205
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:43,000
What?

206
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:45,480
Are you taking this one seriously?

207
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:48,000
- As seriously as I'll ever be, Mami!
- Whoa!

208
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:51,120
Duang.

209
00:12:51,160 --> 00:12:52,280
You scared me.

210
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:53,880
[Have you had anything?]

211
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:56,040
Qin.

212
00:12:57,920 --> 00:13:00,320
You should finish the fruit first
before getting back to your phone.

213
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:02,680
Yes.

214
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:08,760
Was it your university friend?

215
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:10,480
Yes.

216
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:13,160
Have you made a lot of friends there?

217
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:14,400
You should invite some over.

218
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:16,200
We'll make dishes for you guys.

219
00:13:16,680 --> 00:13:17,480
Not that many.

220
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:18,640
It's okay if that's the case, son.

221
00:13:18,680 --> 00:13:20,160
However, mindfully choose your friends.

222
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:23,240
For the sake of your future,

223
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:26,000
having good connections

224
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:27,640
goes a long way.

225
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:30,160
Yes.

226
00:13:40,680 --> 00:13:41,920
Of course, I have.

227
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:46,120
I'd have starved
if I'd waited for you to ask.

228
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:48,480
Qin.

229
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:55,640
I'm sorry.

230
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:57,920
Sweetie, it's okay.

231
00:13:57,960 --> 00:13:59,320
He's probably done.

232
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:04,920
Qin,

233
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:06,680
we're heading out.

234
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:07,960
Would you like to join us?

235
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:09,960
Mm...

236
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:11,640
I can take care of myself.
You two can go.

237
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:14,280
You're not going to ask
where we're off to?

238
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:18,080
Where are you off to?

239
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:21,800
To our office, of course.

240
00:14:22,220 --> 00:14:23,960
Qin, it's probably about time.

241
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,600
You should come with us
when you have the chance.

242
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:28,160
Maybe later.

243
00:14:28,440 --> 00:14:30,000
I have a rehearsal.

244
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:34,920
You do realize what we're doing
is for your future, right?

245
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,920
I know that you're into fragrance.

246
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:37,800
Yes.

247
00:14:38,660 --> 00:14:41,560
I've seen you working in
the fragrance industry since I was little.

248
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:43,920
So why wouldn't I
be passionate about it?

249
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:46,480
Duang.

250
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:50,000
Living alone,
do you get to eat full meals?

251
00:14:50,760 --> 00:14:53,800
I skip meals when I get lazy or forget.

252
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:55,680
But I keep Funan's room clean.

253
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:57,200
You can see it for yourself.

254
00:14:57,360 --> 00:14:58,640
I believe you, Duang.

255
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:01,280
If you need anything,
you have to tell me, okay?

256
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:03,480
You'll be the first to know, I promise.

257
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:05,360
Pinky promise.

258
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:09,720
- Promise.
- Promise.

259
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:11,080
Promise.

260
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:12,360
Promise.

261
00:15:12,520 --> 00:15:13,400
Promise.

262
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:14,600
Promise.

263
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:15,520
Promise.

264
00:15:18,920 --> 00:15:19,840
By the way,

265
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:21,920
on Instagram,

266
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:24,640
your friend tagged you.
You've been singing?

267
00:15:25,560 --> 00:15:27,480
Seniors needed my help.

268
00:15:28,560 --> 00:15:29,400
Hey,

269
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:31,640
Mom showed me the video.

270
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:33,960
You have a natural gift for singing.

271
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:36,000
You should've studied Vocal Performance.

272
00:15:37,760 --> 00:15:39,920
Jazz suits me better.

273
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:44,480
Okay, that's fine.

274
00:15:44,920 --> 00:15:47,000
When you're close to graduating,

275
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:50,040
I'll have you trained
at my friend's record label.

276
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:54,920
Sweetie.

277
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:56,920
I think it's too soon.

278
00:15:56,960 --> 00:15:58,400
Qin is just a freshman.

279
00:15:58,440 --> 00:16:01,450
We should let him choose
what he wants to study.

280
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:06,160
I just want to pave
the way for his career path.

281
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:13,560
What are you having, Qin?

282
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:16,040
Do you know what I want to enjoy?

283
00:16:23,920 --> 00:16:25,720
I want to enjoy a meal with you.

284
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:33,200
Anyone but you.

285
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:36,080
Ouch!

286
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:37,120
- Duang?!
- Ow!

287
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:39,160
Duang!

288
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:40,920
My chest is in pain.

289
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:43,040
What's wrong? Where does it hurt?

290
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:44,800
Oh, that's your heart!

291
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:45,360
Honey!

292
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:46,280
Honey! Duang is in pain!

293
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:47,320
- Duang!
- Take him to a hospital!

294
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:48,480
Duang! You're suffocating!

295
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:50,440
- I told you to take care of your health.
- Tell Dad!

296
00:16:50,480 --> 00:16:52,000
- He's having pain in this area.
- Told you!

297
00:16:52,040 --> 00:16:53,520
- Over here.
- I told you to take care of yourself.

298
00:16:53,560 --> 00:16:55,320
- Use me as an example.
- He fell off this chair.

299
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:58,400
- Duang fell from there.
- Is it hurting that bad, son?

300
00:16:58,440 --> 00:16:59,760
- Ow!
- It's that bad.

301
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:01,280
- We have to take him to a hospital.
- Should we?

302
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:02,760
- Hospital! Which one?!
- Phone! Get the phone!

303
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:03,920
- He has the insurance.
- Come on! Call the hospital!

304
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:12,280
Yeah.

305
00:17:12,460 --> 00:17:13,480
I'm upset.

306
00:17:13,520 --> 00:17:15,280
I haven't come home
in a long while, right?

307
00:17:15,319 --> 00:17:16,800
The moment I met my dad,

308
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:18,400
he turned into a grumbling machine,

309
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:20,160
complaining that
I hadn't been exercising

310
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:22,520
and asking why I didn't stay home
when the semester ended.

311
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:24,280
When I told him about the event,

312
00:17:24,319 --> 00:17:25,839
he told me I was being nonsensical.

313
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:27,079
The same went for Funan.

314
00:17:27,119 --> 00:17:29,400
He piled on me, saying that
I forgot to pay the bills.

315
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:31,200
It felt like I was always in the wrong.

316
00:17:32,220 --> 00:17:33,760
Don't beat yourself up, come on.

317
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:35,000
They're worried about you.

318
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:37,520
They're treating me like I'm a baby boy.

319
00:17:37,760 --> 00:17:39,440
I'm not a kid anymore, am I?

320
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:40,720
You're the youngest son.

321
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:41,840
No matter how old you get,

322
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:44,440
your mom will always see you
as a 3-year-old.

323
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:47,720
What would you know, Western boy?

324
00:17:48,180 --> 00:17:49,480
Rambling does nothing.

325
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:52,040
I wish they'd let me fly
on my own like you are.

326
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:54,440
Aww, it's okay.

327
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:56,280
Don't be upset.

328
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:57,360
Mm...

329
00:17:57,580 --> 00:17:58,580
Let's change the topic.

330
00:17:58,740 --> 00:18:00,000
I have something to brag about.

331
00:18:00,660 --> 00:18:01,860
- Qin is talking to you.
- Qin is talking to me.

332
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:03,600
What?!

333
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:05,600
You knew?

334
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:06,960
I didn't even have to guess.

335
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:07,840
That's it.

336
00:18:08,360 --> 00:18:10,200
Wait, I didn't even get
to talk about it!

337
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:34,660
Jamie, are you listening to me?

338
00:18:34,700 --> 00:18:36,040
I didn't want to hear it, Duang.

339
00:18:36,080 --> 00:18:37,800
That's it. I'm having a drink.

340
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:13,720
What are you doing?

341
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:14,960
Have you gone to bed?

342
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:24,320
[Do you want to meet up tomorrow?]

343
00:19:25,840 --> 00:19:28,160
[Everyone is coming]

344
00:19:30,520 --> 00:19:31,320
[Calling]

345
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:41,640
Hello?

346
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:43,640
You called me?

347
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:45,080
It was an accident.

348
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:47,800
Right, an accident it was.

349
00:19:47,840 --> 00:19:50,400
Just tell me if you miss me.

350
00:19:52,060 --> 00:19:53,520
You should get your brain checked.

351
00:19:54,520 --> 00:19:56,160
Oh, you...

352
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:57,200
You're making me blush.

353
00:19:57,560 --> 00:19:59,380
All I have in my brain is you.

354
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:03,120
What have you done today?

355
00:20:03,620 --> 00:20:04,480
I've been staying home.

356
00:20:04,880 --> 00:20:07,200
Oh, so have I!
I've also been at home.

357
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:08,920
But...

358
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:10,280
Funan is so annoying.

359
00:20:10,820 --> 00:20:11,820
Your older brother?

360
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,160
You remembered?

361
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:14,840
Your whole family has weird names.

362
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,760
Well, my parents are archaeologists.

363
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:18,600
That's why they name us
after old coins.

364
00:20:18,720 --> 00:20:19,720
Funan.

365
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:23,040
Duang, short for PhodDuang.

366
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:25,200
Your name is also weird.

367
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:27,040
I've never heard of it.

368
00:20:27,280 --> 00:20:28,880
It's Qin. How is it strange?

369
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:30,640
Is there a meaning behind it?

370
00:20:31,720 --> 00:20:33,440
The meaning is twofold.

371
00:20:33,760 --> 00:20:35,000
It either means 'to criticize'

372
00:20:35,320 --> 00:20:36,560
or 'beauty.'

373
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:38,000
I think yours is the latter.

374
00:20:38,240 --> 00:20:39,520
Your name means 'beauty.'

375
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:41,520
If you see the negative, then it is.

376
00:20:41,560 --> 00:20:42,760
The same goes for the opposite.

377
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:46,000
My mom says it's natural
to have good and bad sides.

378
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:47,200
Mm.

379
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:49,440
Sounds sophisticated

380
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:51,400
and extraordinary.

381
00:20:56,720 --> 00:20:58,640
You called me
to say sweet dreams, right?

382
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:00,960
I know what you're trying to do.

383
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:02,240
Suit yourself.

384
00:21:02,280 --> 00:21:05,000
I miss you to death, you know?

385
00:21:06,700 --> 00:21:07,700
I'm ending the call.

386
00:21:07,740 --> 00:21:08,520
Oh, wait...

387
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:10,560
Okay, see you tomorrow, babe.

388
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:12,000
Good night.

389
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:15,800
Huh?

390
00:21:16,640 --> 00:21:17,480
Come on.

391
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:19,200
I wasn't finished!

392
00:22:06,260 --> 00:22:08,040
Don't forget to dream of me

393
00:22:08,520 --> 00:22:09,920
so that you'll have good dreams.

394
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:25,880
'To criticize'

395
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:27,840
and 'beauty.'

396
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:29,560
I like both meanings.

397
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:51,360
What? You're leaving already?

398
00:22:52,270 --> 00:22:53,600
You're on a date
with a girl, aren't you?

399
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:57,280
A little bird told me that you are.

400
00:22:57,320 --> 00:22:58,240
You're partially right.

401
00:22:58,400 --> 00:22:59,400
But I'm not seeing a girl.

402
00:23:00,280 --> 00:23:01,280
Seriously?

403
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:03,400
My heart calls for this person.

404
00:23:03,440 --> 00:23:05,720
Gender isn't my concern.

405
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:10,000
Don't forget to introduce
the person to me.

406
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:12,580
Just you wait.

407
00:23:13,720 --> 00:23:14,600
Okay.

408
00:23:15,220 --> 00:23:16,040
Bye-bye.

409
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:24,280
Duang.

410
00:23:24,760 --> 00:23:25,400
Yes?

411
00:23:25,440 --> 00:23:26,440
Where are you off to?

412
00:23:27,140 --> 00:23:28,640
To... To a dance practice.

413
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:29,800
- Huh?
- A dance practice.

414
00:23:29,840 --> 00:23:30,840
Wait, wait...

415
00:23:31,280 --> 00:23:32,360
What dance?

416
00:23:32,480 --> 00:23:35,280
It's for the event I told you about.

417
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:39,800
My professor knows about it, too.

418
00:23:39,840 --> 00:23:41,560
I'm not doing anything bad.

419
00:23:41,740 --> 00:23:45,000
Moreover, I've made a promise
to make this a good performance.

420
00:23:45,040 --> 00:23:46,320
That's why I have to practice a lot.

421
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:50,680
In that case,

422
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:52,200
I'll have Funan drive you there.

423
00:23:52,360 --> 00:23:53,720
- Funan, drive him to...
- Oh, Dad!

424
00:23:54,100 --> 00:23:55,080
No need!

425
00:23:55,120 --> 00:23:56,640
I can drive.

426
00:23:57,640 --> 00:23:58,640
Moreover,

427
00:23:58,680 --> 00:24:01,000
you're sending Funan
to keep tabs on me, aren't you?

428
00:24:01,520 --> 00:24:03,720
It's just an ordinary event.

429
00:24:03,760 --> 00:24:05,520
I'll send you
pictures of me there later.

430
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:06,960
Duang.

431
00:24:07,280 --> 00:24:08,880
When you do something,

432
00:24:08,920 --> 00:24:11,160
be passionate and serious about it.

433
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:12,760
Don't slack off too much, okay?

434
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:14,880
Yes, I know that, Dad.

435
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:18,280
I know that
I have to own up to my words.

436
00:24:18,520 --> 00:24:20,280
If I don't,

437
00:24:20,320 --> 00:24:22,160
I'll seem unreliable

438
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:23,520
and incompetent.

439
00:24:26,500 --> 00:24:27,800
I'm worried about you, you see.

440
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:29,760
Right.

441
00:24:30,440 --> 00:24:31,800
I'll be going now. Bye-bye.

442
00:24:31,920 --> 00:24:32,840
Get going, son.

443
00:24:37,310 --> 00:24:38,480
Stay safe on the road.

444
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:39,450
Thank you.

445
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:46,920
You called me, Dad?

446
00:24:47,440 --> 00:24:48,240
Come.

447
00:24:49,440 --> 00:24:51,240
I want you to talk to your brother

448
00:24:52,040 --> 00:24:54,640
and warn him not to slack off too much.

449
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:56,600
Oh, I thought it'd be something else.

450
00:24:56,760 --> 00:24:59,480
I've been telling him that.

451
00:24:59,880 --> 00:25:02,640
Lately, he's gotten
a lot better, you see.

452
00:25:02,800 --> 00:25:04,000
He's still young.

453
00:25:04,360 --> 00:25:05,720
It's good to have you keep tabs on him.

454
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:10,040
He said that the event he's working on
has something to do with dancing.

455
00:25:10,080 --> 00:25:10,920
Mm.

456
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:13,200
Alright, Dad.

457
00:25:15,240 --> 00:25:16,840
I slowed down the music.

458
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:19,800
The seniors helped with the choreography

459
00:25:19,840 --> 00:25:21,120
to match the slower tempo.

460
00:25:21,160 --> 00:25:22,120
Let's give it a go.

461
00:25:23,200 --> 00:25:24,920
One, two,

462
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:25,960
three,

463
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:27,400
- Three...
- four.

464
00:25:30,120 --> 00:25:30,840
One more time.

465
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:34,000
Your hands go like this,
each forming an L shape.

466
00:25:34,040 --> 00:25:35,040
Three and four.

467
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:37,200
Gosh, my arms are dying.

468
00:25:38,480 --> 00:25:39,240
Down.

469
00:25:39,430 --> 00:25:40,160
Down.

470
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:41,480
Two fingers. Up, then bam, bam.

471
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:44,320
Oh! I need to film
a video for my parents!

472
00:25:53,080 --> 00:25:58,440
♫I'll keep on flirting,
don't try to avoid me♫

473
00:25:58,480 --> 00:26:03,240
♫'Cause I won't stop
till you fall for me♫

474
00:26:03,280 --> 00:26:07,800
♫I'll keep on flirting,
I won't stop, I guarantee♫

475
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:14,360
♫I'll love you hard,
and once you say yes, I'll set you free♫

476
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:21,360
All good?
You can remember it now, can't you?

477
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:22,640
I can.

478
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:23,680
- Okay.
- Three,

479
00:26:23,720 --> 00:26:26,080
four, five, and six.

480
00:26:26,440 --> 00:26:27,440
Seven, eight...

481
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:28,280
Hey!

482
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:32,680
Are you good?

483
00:26:34,040 --> 00:26:35,040
Let's call it here today.

484
00:26:35,640 --> 00:26:36,640
Why?

485
00:26:37,100 --> 00:26:39,080
I'm about to nail it.

486
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:41,540
Stop.

487
00:26:42,320 --> 00:26:43,320
Do as I say.

488
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:46,720
Okay.

489
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:56,280
[Kate Teaw]

490
00:27:03,440 --> 00:27:05,440
How was the practice?

491
00:27:06,240 --> 00:27:08,800
[Good morning]

492
00:27:12,040 --> 00:27:14,200
[Was your body not cooperating?]

493
00:27:53,480 --> 00:27:54,480
When are you going to dig in?

494
00:27:59,620 --> 00:28:00,720
Well, I...

495
00:28:01,360 --> 00:28:02,560
I'd like to apologize to you first.

496
00:28:06,200 --> 00:28:07,080
I...

497
00:28:08,560 --> 00:28:09,640
I did so poorly.

498
00:28:09,680 --> 00:28:11,480
I mean, I tried,

499
00:28:11,600 --> 00:28:13,080
but it looked like I didn't, right?

500
00:28:14,020 --> 00:28:15,520
I feel like this isn't my cup of tea.

501
00:28:17,600 --> 00:28:18,800
Take your time.

502
00:28:19,040 --> 00:28:20,240
Were you born to be a dance machine?

503
00:28:22,240 --> 00:28:25,990
Maybe I haven't tried hard enough.

504
00:28:26,360 --> 00:28:27,880
I could see that you were trying.

505
00:28:31,740 --> 00:28:33,240
Aww...

506
00:28:33,880 --> 00:28:34,880
Dig in already.

507
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:53,920
This whole bowl is yours!

508
00:28:53,960 --> 00:28:55,560
Finish it. I'll order another one.

509
00:28:58,120 --> 00:28:59,360
Righto.

510
00:29:10,040 --> 00:29:11,040
Let me do it.

511
00:29:11,320 --> 00:29:12,360
Let me drive you home.

512
00:29:16,320 --> 00:29:18,200
What's up with your tone?

513
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:22,120
Someone here likes it.

514
00:29:25,760 --> 00:29:27,160
But he keeps his mouth shut.

515
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:38,400
You think so?

516
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:45,240
Want to pry it open?

517
00:30:05,640 --> 00:30:06,800
So lame.

518
00:30:22,760 --> 00:30:23,360
Jamie.

519
00:30:23,600 --> 00:30:24,250
Jamie...

520
00:30:24,560 --> 00:30:25,720
Jamie, come here!

521
00:30:26,440 --> 00:30:27,680
Warrior, come this way.

522
00:30:27,920 --> 00:30:29,200
- Come here.
- It's good to see you.

523
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:30,400
Here's your secret weapon.

524
00:30:30,880 --> 00:30:31,760
A drink, please.

525
00:30:33,040 --> 00:30:33,720
Wait...

526
00:30:34,320 --> 00:30:35,520
Your buddy, Duang,
isn't here with you?

527
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:36,640
No.

528
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:38,420
He's on a lover-boy mission.

529
00:30:39,600 --> 00:30:40,520
He's in a relationship?

530
00:30:40,560 --> 00:30:42,440
No, he's trying to win
his crush's heart.

531
00:30:42,480 --> 00:30:43,800
Oh, okay.

532
00:30:44,240 --> 00:30:45,240
And what about you?

533
00:30:45,400 --> 00:30:46,280
What will it be for tonight?

534
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:47,480
Who is on your radar?

535
00:30:50,320 --> 00:30:51,320
I don't have any.

536
00:30:51,760 --> 00:30:53,560
Today, I'm going for an ambush.

537
00:30:53,960 --> 00:30:55,240
I'm diving in headfirst.

538
00:30:55,640 --> 00:30:58,420
Alright! That's my bro.

539
00:31:01,620 --> 00:31:03,080
"If you give someone a fish,

540
00:31:03,520 --> 00:31:05,160
all they'll have is that fish.

541
00:31:05,720 --> 00:31:07,720
But if you teach someone how to fish,

542
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:09,800
they'll get to have
fish for their whole life."

543
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:11,440
What's gotten into you?

544
00:31:12,080 --> 00:31:13,080
This is who I am.

545
00:31:13,200 --> 00:31:14,080
Here, bottoms up.

546
00:31:23,960 --> 00:31:25,280
I went to the toilet.

547
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:34,600
Go and get him.

548
00:31:35,600 --> 00:31:37,440
He never picks the same person twice,

549
00:31:38,200 --> 00:31:39,800
so don't worry about the repercussions,

550
